Review of: Hue to Hoi An or Hoi An to Hue by car via Hai Van pass, monkey mountain, beaches
Written March 6, 2024
Jessica
Canada9 contributions
Exciting trip !
It's great that these 3 attractions are all recognized by UNESCO as world cultural heritage sites. The first destination was the mausoleum of Khai Dinh - the 12th Emperor of the Nguyen Dynasty. What impressed me most in the mausoleum were the details assembled from thousands of pieces of porcelain, porcelain and glass - combining them into extremely fine paintings. cunning. Lunch at the restaurant is typical dishes of Hue people, diverse dishes with very delicious flavors - suitable for my taste. Continue moving to Thien Mu Pagoda, an ancient pagoda located right next to the romantic Perfume River. The tour guide tells about the history and introduces in detail the locations in the Imperial Citadel of Hue - one of the largest-scale works in Vietnamese history. This place is quiet and fresh, making me want to stay here forever. I found this trip experience very worthwhile, everything from the people, the food, the weather to the tour guide were all great! Please try and experience it!
